<article class="article">
  
    <h2 class="article__title"><a href="/blog/jekyll-3-5-2/">Jekyll 3.5.2 is here</a></h2>
  
  
  <section class="article__meta">
    
      <ul class="article__tags">
        
          
          
            
            
              <li class="article__tag"><a href="/blog/tags/announcement/" class="article__tag__link bg--green">Announcement</a></li>
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
        
          
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
              <li class="article__tag"><a href="/blog/tags/jekyll/" class="article__tag__link bg--red">Jekyll</a></li>
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
        
          
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
              <li class="article__tag"><a href="/blog/tags/github/" class="article__tag__link bg--dark-gray">GitHub</a></li>
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
        
      </ul>
    
    
    <time class="article__date" datetime="2017-08-24T00:00:00-04:00">Aug 24, 2017</time>
    
  </section>
  
  <section class="article__content">
    

    

    
      <p>Recently GitHub Pages upgraded to Jekyll 3.5.2, and we‚Äôve now made it our default to match.</p>

<p>This update includes a few enhancements and bug fixes, most notably one which should dramatically speed up generation of your site! In testing <a href="https://jekyllrb.com">jekyllrb.com</a>, generation went from 18 seconds down to 8.</p>

<p>For a full list of revisions <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/news/2017/08/12/jekyll-3-5-2-released/">check out the release notes</a>.</p>

<p>If you are still using Jekyll 3.4, here‚Äôs everything that‚Äôs new in 3.5 so far:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Jekyll now uses Liquid 4, the latest! It comes with whitespace control, new filters <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">concat</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">compact</code>, loop performance improvements and <a href="https://github.com/Shopify/liquid/blob/master/History.md#400--2016-12-14--branch-4-0-stable">many fixes</a>.</li>
  <li>Themes can specify dependencies and Jekyll will require those. This makes it easier for theme writers to use plugins.</li>
  <li>The <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">gems</code> key in the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">_config.yml</code> is now <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">plugins</code>. This is backwards-compatible, as Jekyll will gracefully upgrade gems to plugins if you use the former.</li>
  <li>Filters like sort now allow you to sort based on a subvalue, e.g. <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">{% assign sorted = site.posts | sort: "image.alt_text" %}</code>.</li>
  <li>You can now use tab-separated data files.</li>
  <li>Using <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">layout: none</code> will now produce a file with no layout. Equivalent to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">layout: null</code>, with the exception that none is a truthy value and won‚Äôt be overwritten by front matter defaults.</li>
  <li>Dramatically faster site generation!</li>
  <li>Lots <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/news/2017/06/15/jekyll-3-5-0-released/">more</a> <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/news/2017/07/17/jekyll-3-5-1-released/">bug</a> <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/news/2017/08/12/jekyll-3-5-2-released/">fixes</a>.</li>
</ul>

    
    
      <a href="/blog/jekyll-3-5-2/" class="article__content__more">Read more</a>
    
  </section>
</article>


  

