    <h2 class="article__title"><a href="/blog/github-pages/">Now publishing to GitHub¬†Pages</a></h2>
  
  
  <section class="article__meta">
    
      <ul class="article__tags">
        
          
          
            
            
              <li class="article__tag"><a href="/blog/tags/announcement/" class="article__tag__link bg--green">Announcement</a></li>
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
        
          
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
              <li class="article__tag"><a href="/blog/tags/github/" class="article__tag__link bg--dark-gray">GitHub</a></li>
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
            
            
          
        
      </ul>
    
    
    <time class="article__date" datetime="2014-06-04T09:00:00-04:00">Jun 04, 2014</time>
    
  </section>
  
  <section class="article__content">
    

    
    <p>
      <a href="/blog/github-pages/"><img src="/uploads/github.svg" alt="Now publishing to GitHub¬†Pages" /></a>
    </p>
    

    
      <p>Exciting news! Starting today you can now publish your sites from Siteleaf to <a href="https://pages.github.com">GitHub¬†Pages</a>.</p>

<p>GitHub Pages is a solid choice for static web hosting, especially if you already use <a href="http://github.com">GitHub</a> to manage your theme code‚Äîand it‚Äôs clear a lot of our users <a href="https://github.com/siteleaf/siteleaf-themes/wiki/Siteleaf-themes-on-Github">already do</a>.</p>

<h3 id="why-github-pages">Why GitHub Pages?</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>It‚Äôs fast!</strong> Check out this comparison by <a href="http://www.jeremymorgan.com/blog/programming/how-fast-are-github-pages/">Jeremy Morgan</a>.</li>
  <li><strong>It‚Äôs powered by a global CDN</strong>, from the folks at <a href="http://www.fastly.com/customers/github/">Fastly</a>.</li>
  <li><strong>It‚Äôs version controlled!</strong> Every publish is a commit, so you can see revisions and revert back to any publish state.</li>
  <li><strong>And there‚Äôs no extra cost</strong>, GitHub Pages is included with your GitHub account.</li>
</ul>

<figure>
<img src="/uploads/github-commit.png" />
<figcaption>Every publish from Siteleaf shows as a commit on GitHub.com</figcaption>
</figure>

    
    
      <a href="/blog/github-pages/" class="article__content__more">Read more</a>
    
  </section>
